## 1. Overview

### 1.1 Purpose

This document defines the complete technical requirements, system architecture, data models, API contracts, AI integration patterns, security requirements, compliance framework, and testing strategy for the Finance Buddy application. It is the authoritative reference for all engineering decisions from MVP through full product.

### 1.2 Product Summary

Finance Buddy is an AI-first personal finance companion targeting beginners aged 16–25. The product is organized around four core pillars:

1. **Learn** — Adaptive financial education with AI-generated explanations
2. **Budget** — AI-powered budget tracking with spending insights
3. **Invest (Simulated)** — Paper trading portfolio with explainable AI recommendations
4. **Ask** — Always-available AI chatbot companion

The application extends beyond investing into a comprehensive financial decision-making suite including bank selection, credit card comparison, savings plans, debt management, and behavioral coaching.

### 1.3 Core Principle

> *"The AI provides probabilistic insights and educational explanations — not financial advice."*

The AI is positioned as **educational guidance + decision support**, NOT an autonomous financial advisor.

